{"action_a_id": "move_toxic", "action_b_id": "move_wing_attack", "action_tags": {"move_toxic": ["fits_boss_style", "too_passive"], "move_wing_attack": ["scary_pressure", "uses_public_info"]}, "choice": "b_better", "created_at": "2026-05-10T12:40:47+00:00", "fixture_id": "koga_crobat_vs_alakazam_toxic_or_attack", "note": "This one is just non-sensical. The point of Toxic is to help chip a pokemon slowly. Crobat just straight up kills Alakazam with Wing Attack. It's like choosing between earning $10 a day or getting a million dollars right now. You don't need the incremental damage of Toxic when you can bring it all the way to 0 immediately.", "preferred_action_id": "move_wing_attack", "reason_tags": [], "source_team_hash": "8c8c4b4d836bd052", "state_version": 2, "tool_version": "boss-ai-preference-v0"}
{"action_a_id": "move_dragon_dance", "action_b_id": "move_outrage", "action_tags": {"move_dragon_dance": ["calculated_risk", "scary_pressure"], "move_outrage": ["keeps_tempo", "reduces_risk"]}, "choice": "needs_context", "created_at": "2026-05-10T12:50:38+00:00", "fixture_id": "lance_dragonite_vs_suicune_champion_ace", "note": "Genuinely ambiguous because hidden Ice coverage flips every move's value here. Dragon Dance is amazing if Suicune doesn't have Ice (with DD, Outrage's 3HKO becomes a 2HKO so no turn really lost setting up), but +2 Dragonite walks into a 4x Ice OHKO if it does. Outrage chips ~30% AND probes for Ice - if Suicune has it, the next turn reveals it; if not, that's safe chip to weaken Suicune for the rest of Lance's team. The current roster changes the upstream answer: instead of old Aerodactyl/Starmie pivots, Lance can scout or preserve through Kingdra, Gyarados, Steelix, Ampharos, or Yanma depending on public coverage risk. If forced at this moment, Outrage still tilts ahead for chip + information value, but the choice stays needs_context because the deeper lesson is ace timing and pivot selection before Dragonite is exposed.", "preferred_action_id": null, "reason_tags": [], "source_team_hash": "baea92b836fc8f2e", "state_version": 2, "tool_version": "boss-ai-preference-v0"}
{"action_a_id": "move_explosion", "action_b_id": "move_earthquake", "action_tags": {"move_earthquake": ["misses_public_threat"], "move_explosion": ["keeps_tempo", "reduces_risk"]}, "choice": "a_better", "created_at": "2026-05-10T17:51:43+00:00", "fixture_id": "brock_golem_vs_vaporeon_explosion_question", "note": "Earthquake is definitely bad unless you predict a switch because Vaporeon will OHKO with any water move so may as well explode to trade. However staying in at all is a bad play because Vaporeon outspeeds and kills every time with water. Switching to Omastar is the best play, but I didn't suggest that because a below 50% HP slow pokemon like golem may sturggle to get value later as it will often always be outsped and so it's better to sacrifice it to get a clean switch into a full health Omastar rather than Omastar take chip damage switching in. And if the player overpredicts and doesn't use water move, Explosion will nail something. But Explosion and switch out are both very close in scoring and you should switch it up to avoid being too predictable.", "preferred_action_id": "move_explosion", "reason_tags": [], "source_team_hash": "1dc670c148bc905f", "state_version": 2, "tool_version": "boss-ai-preference-v0"}
